# SMA-437 Layer-1 per-netns default-deny — forkd tap/FORWARD topology.
# In forkd's per-child netns the guest sits behind ${GUEST_IF} and its egress is
# ROUTED (FORWARD chain) out via ${UPLINK_IF} to the uplink. The guest's packets
# do NOT traverse this netns's OUTPUT chain (OUTPUT belongs to processes running
# inside the netns, e.g. the egress proxy). So Layer-1 filters FORWARD, dropping
# guest(${GUEST_IF}) -> uplink(${UPLINK_IF}) forwarding. This blocks raw/non-proxy
# egress, DNS exfil, QUIC, etc., while leaving ACCEPTed: the controller->agent
# path (${UPLINK_IF}->${GUEST_IF}), the guest->in-netns-proxy path (local
# delivery to the ${GUEST_IF} host IP), and the proxy->upstream path (OUTPUT).
*filter
:FORWARD ACCEPT [0:0]
-A FORWARD -i ${GUEST_IF} -o ${UPLINK_IF} -j DROP
COMMIT
